PublicRemarks: For Sale or Lease. Unique opportunity to acquire a well-maintained 7,409 SF industrial warehouse building, featuring renovated officespace, new roof in 2022, dock and grade-level loading doors, and large gravel parking lot. Also included is a bonus 2 bed + den / 2bath residential home located directly adjacent to the warehouse building. The home features many recent upgrades and provides an excellent opportunity for additional rental income, or conversion to additional office space. The property, which fronts on the Rails toTrails project, is located just a minute's drive from the new Exit 5A off Hwy 103, a 15 minute drive to Bayers Lake Business Park, and 30 minutes to downtown Halifax. Many amenities including restaurants, schools, shopping, inns, cottages, and beautiful sandybeaches are all minutes away in the larger communities of Hubbards and Tantallon. The Seller has obtained a satisfactory Phase I Environmental Site Assessment which will be provided to the Purchaser. (228357916)

PublicRemarks: This vacant parcel is a part of the Progress Drive Business Park in the Town of Aylmer. It is located near the high traffic corner of John Street North and Progress Drive. The zoning for the parcel permits a variety of business park and industrial uses. The wooded section of the parcel will be retained by the Town of Aylmer.  Asking price is $250,000 per acre, but there is the potential for price adjustment for more desirable intended future land uses.  Municipal services located at John Street North and Progress Drive. Great location for a variety of uses including warehouse, manufacturing, commercial storage, large retail stores, wholesale establishments, offices, drive-thru/ restaurant and more.  Seller is the Corporation of the Town of Aylmer. Taxes will be reassessed for the new owner. (66651875)

PublicRemarks: Industrial lot for sale located off District Road 118 in Bracebridge. Total subdivision is over 40AC of industrial serviced lots starting at $350,000 per AC. Individual lots range from 1-8 AC. Lot breakdown can be found within photos. Zoning varies among lots from M1-7 to M1-10. M1 zoning (Business Park Industrial) allows for many different Industrial and Commercial uses. The lots in the Business Park abutting the railway are zoned Business Park Industrial Special – 7 (M1-7). The railway setback requires a building setback of 15 metres from the lot line that abuts the railway. All lots would be subject to Site Plan Control. Bracebridge development charges are currently $0 allowing for financial incentive. See brochure for more information regarding lots, financial incentives and demographics. (67056054)

PublicRemarks: If you are searching for a country property for exploring, hiking, enjoying the wildlife and thousands of trees, including sugar maple, white pine, white cedar, ash and walnut then this is the property for you. This pristine acreage has been lovingly cared for and explored daily by it's current owner of over 35 years. It could be considered a wildlife refuge as seen with the many deer tracks, wolf tracks and coyote tracks that frequent the property. There is a man-made pond that has been cleared of vegetation in the past few years. Fronting on Grey Road 29 within 20 minutes of Owen Sound and located 15 minutes to Meaford, 30 Minutes to Blue Mountain Resorts and 40 minutes to Collingwood. This is a very special acreage for those that have been searching for a country property and is also suitable for a country home. (66980611)

PublicRemarks: Discover a one-of-a-kind opportunity to own 13 acres of recreational land on the picturesque Libby Island. This tranquil oasis, nestled on the Rideau waterway, offers the perfect private escape for you and your loved ones. Located just a short drive from Kemptville and an easy commute from Ottawa, this property provides a fantastic weekend camping option that's not too far from home! The island can be accessed via boat or car over the land causeway from Foster Memorial Park. With over 2000 feet of pristine shoreline, you'll have endless opportunities to explore and enjoy the beauty of the area. The property is environmentally protected, and it's a natural habitat for various species of wildlife and flora. Embark on exciting adventures and create unforgettable memories on Libby Island! PublicRemarks: Your dream home building plot awaits! Rare offering: almost 6.5 acres of serene treed land on a quiet cul-de-sac steps away from the Mississippi River. A stunning bucolic setting w/rural zoning, bordering environmentally protected land, thus securing future privacy - sunbathe in the nude!  Recently extended culvert, approx. 100 metres of driveway base already installed & 1+ acre cleared for future build site. A natural scenery lined with primarily pine & oak trees w/hints of maple, ash, cedar, birch & ironwood. A symphony of gentle slopes, rock & flat areas sweep the landscape. Excellent local for nature & outdoor enthusiasts: nearby gems include Morris Island Conservation Area, Fitzroy Provincial Park, Ottawa River & OFSC snowmobile trails. Hike, canoe, snowshoe & more! Survey & property maps available. Check out drone video link! 30 min.to Kanata, less than 15 min. to Arnprior & 15 min.to Quyon Ferry. Lot is HST exempt. Please don't enter onto the property without consent. (26898428)
